# Parent Information

Everything you need to know to prepare your camper for an amazing week at Bear Lake Camp.

## Check-In & Check-Out

{% cardGrid cols="2" width="auto" height="auto" backgroundColor="" %}
{% contentCard
   icon="Clock"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Check-In Times"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
**Sunday**: 4:30-5:30pm at the Dining Hall

**Primary Overnight Exception**: Thursday Morning at 10:00am

Please arrive during the designated window so we can properly welcome your camper and get them settled into their cabin.
{% /contentCard %}

{% contentCard
   icon="Car"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Pick-Up Times"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
**Friday Night**: 6:30pm

**Junior 3 Exception**: Thursday at 6:30pm

Check out your camper at their cabin and collect their belongings.

Stop by the Snack Shack to get your left-over money, camp picture (if ordered), and browse BLC gear for sale.

Please arrive on time - counselors are released when all campers are picked up.
{% /contentCard %}
{% /cardGrid %}

## What Happens at Check-In

{% sectionCard variant="default" background="none" width="auto" %}
When you arrive, you will:

1. **Head to the tent near the parking lot**
1. **Our LITs will happily collect and deliver your luggage** on the Bear Lake Express
1. **Head to Check In at the Dining Hall Porch**
1. **Settle your balance**
1. **Get your cabin assignment**
1. **Head to the cabin to meet your counselor and choose a bed**
1. **Say your goodbyes before opening program** 5:30

*Pro tip: Arrive a few minutes early to walk around, see the waterfront, and ask any last-minute questions!*
{% /sectionCard %}

