## Staying Connected

{% cardGrid cols="2" width="auto" height="auto" backgroundColor="" %}
{% contentCard
   icon="MessageCircle"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Communication Policy"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
We operate by the core value of "Awayness" our during the week to help campers fully engage in the camp experience. This means that our camp program is "screen free."

- Campers do not have access to phones
- If you need to reach your camper for an emergency, call the camp office and leave a message.
- Leadership staff will facilitate a call home if your camper is struggling
{% /contentCard %}

{% contentCard
   icon="Camera"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Regular Updates"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
We'll keep you in the loop!

- **Photo Slideshows posted** on our Facebook/Instagram page
- You're welcome to send letters or care packages (no food please)
{% /contentCard %}
{% /cardGrid %}

## Write to Your Camper

{% cardGrid cols="3" width="auto" height="auto" backgroundColor="" %}
{% contentCard
   icon="Mail"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Snail Mail"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
Our campers love to get mail at camp! Send letters, postcards, or packages to:

**Camper Name c/o**
**Bear Lake Camp**
**1805 S. 16th St.**
**Albion, IN 46701**

*Mail sent Monday or Tuesday will typically arrive before camp ends.*
{% /contentCard %}

{% contentCard
   icon="Gift"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Care Package Tips"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
- **Do** send encouraging notes, stickers, small items
- **Do** include stamps and addressed postcards
- **Don't** send food (dietary reasons and cabin critters!)
- **Don't** send expensive items that could get lost
{% /contentCard %}

{% contentCard
   icon="MessageCircle"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Camper E-Mail"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
Send an E-mail to your camper!

- Email to: camper@bearlakecamp.com
- Put your camper's name and cabin number in the subject line
- Please refrain from sending pictures or links as e-mails must be printed out for campers

\*Please honor this courtesy by only sending one email to your camper/day to help us reduce excessive paper waste.
{% /contentCard %}
{% /cardGrid %}

## Pray for Your Camper

{% sectionCard variant="elevated" background="none" width="auto" %}
We believe **PRAYER** is a vital part of the ministry at Bear Lake Camp. You are encouraged to pray throughout the day. Coordinated staff prayer times take place daily at 7:00am, 5:00pm, and 10:30pm.

**Pray daily that your camper and others will:**

- Be **CHANGED** by encountering Jesus
- Make a **decision to GROW** in their faith
- Be **EQUIPPED** to read and engage Scripture
- Build **healthy relationships** with others
- Experience the **love of God**
- Sense **God's presence** daily
- Enjoy a **fun, safe week**

Also pray for your camper's specific needs and for our camp staff!
{% /sectionCard %}

## Health & Safety

{% cardGrid cols="2" width="auto" height="auto" backgroundColor="" %}
{% contentCard
   icon="Stethoscope"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Medical Care"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
- **Camp nurse on-site 24/7**
- Hospital 15 minutes away
- All staff trained in First Aid and CPR
- We'll contact you for any health concerns
{% /contentCard %}

{% contentCard
   icon="Pill"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Medications"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
- Turn in all medications to nurse at check-in
- Medications must be in **original containers**
- Include **written dosage instructions**
- Nurse dispenses all medications on schedule
- Campers may NOT keep meds in cabins (exceptions made for rescue inhalers and T1 Diabetes)
{% /contentCard %}
{% /cardGrid %}

